<div id="hitoria">
  <section class="slice bg-3 no-padding">
    <div class="w-section inverse">
      <div class="">
        <ul class="timeline">
          <li class="year">2011 - 2018</li>
          <li class="event">
            <div class="event-date">
              <p>CADU carried out the placement of local notes (“CADU 18”) for an amount of Ps.500 million, unsecured and a 5-year term, being the longer maturity term of CADU’s local notes.</p>
              <small> 2018</small>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="event mover">
            <div class="event-date">
              <p>CADU inaugurated Allure, a residential complex facing the Caribbean Sea, surrounded by natural beauties, providing security and over-the-top amenities.</p>
              <small> 2017</small>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="event mover">
            <div class="event-date">
              <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-12">
                  <img src="/assets/cadu/images/content/longi.jpg" class="img-responsive" alt="CADU BMV">
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="event ">
            <div class="event-date">
              <p>CADU inaugurated the first development of the Long Island residential complex: York Homes. With this opening, CADU reaffirms its leadership in Quintana Roo and moves towards creating a more solid sales mix, increasing the middle-income residential segment participation in homes sold revenue.</p>
              <small> 2017</small>
            </div>

          </li>
          <li class="event mover">
            <div class="event-date">
              <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-12">
                  <img src="/assets/cadu/images/content/astoria.jpg" class="img-responsive" alt="CADU BMV">
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="event mover">
            <div class="event-date">
              <p>Middle-income home sales in Cancun and Mexico Valley recorded an average sale price of Ps.1.8 million.</p>
              <small> 2016</small>
            </div>

          </li>
          <li class="event">
            <div class="event-date">
              <p>With the proceeds from its IPO, CADU plans to continue with its growth plan focused on expanding its offering towards products with greater profitability and prices ranges.</p>

              <small> 2015</small>
            </div>

          </li>
          <li class="event mover">
            <div class="event-date">

              <p>CADU carried out a Initial Public Offering on the Bolsa Mexicana de Valores (Mexican Stock Exchange) under the ticker symbol “CADU”, marking the return of the housing sector to the Mexican Equity Market around ten years after the last issuance.</p>

              <small> 2015</small>
            </div>

          </li>

          <li class="event ">
            <div class="event-date">
              <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-12">
                  <img src="/assets/cadu/images/content/cadu-bmv.jpg" class="img-responsive" alt="CADU BMV">
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="event mover">
            <div class="event-date">
              <p>The third placement of unsecured local notes (“CADU 15”) was completed for Ps.400 million.</p>

              <small> 2015</small>
            </div>

          </li>
          <li class="event mover">
            <div class="event-date">
              <p>The second issuance of local notes was carried out (“CADU 14”) for Ps.300 million, accompanied by a 50% guarantee from the Sociedad Hipotecaria Federal (Federal Mortgage Society), and obtaining a credit rating of “A+” by Fitch Ratings.</p>

              <small> 2014</small>
            </div>

          </li>
          <li class="event mover">
            <div class="event-date">

              <p>CADU receives the Mejores Empresas Mexicanas award (Best Mexican Companies) granted by Banamex, Deloitte and the Tecnologico de Monterrey.</p>

              <small> 2014</small>
            </div>

          </li>
          <li class="event ">
            <div class="event-date">
              <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-12">
                  <img src="/assets/cadu/images/content/2014.png" class="img-responsive" alt="CADU">
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="event">
            <div class="event-date">
              <p>CADU initiates the commercialization process of homes in Guanajuato and the State of Mexico.</p>
              <small> 2013</small>
            </div>

          </li>
          <li class="event mover">
            <div class="event-date">
              <p>CADU ranked 8th among all Mexican home builders in mortgage credits granted by the Instituto del Fondo Nacional de la Vivienda para los Trabajadores (Mexican Federal Institute for Worker´s Housing, known as INFONAVIT by its Spanish acronym).</p>
              <small> 2012</small>
            </div>

          </li>
          <li class="event">
            <div class="event-date">
              <p>CADU completes its first placement of local notes (“CADU 12”) for Ps.300 million, accompanied by a 48% guarantee from Nacional Financiera (the Mexican state-owned development bank, known as NAFIN by its Spanish acronym), and obtaining a credit rating of “A+” by Fitch Ratings.</p>
              <small> 2012</small>
            </div>

          </li>
          <li class="year">2001 -2010</li>
          <li class="event  offset-first">
            <div class="event-date">
              <p>CADU´s bylaws were reformed in order to adopt the Code of Best Corporate Practices, with the incorporation of independent board members.</p>
              <small> 2009</small>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="event">
            <div class="event-date">
              <p>CADU becomes the leading player in the development of Affordable-Entry homes in the state of Quintana Roo.</p>
              <small> 2008</small>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="event ">
            <div class="event-date">
              <p>Corpovael, S.A. de C.V. (CADU) is established as a holding company of the shares of all its subsidiaries, with the purpose of consolidating them.</p>
              <small> 2007</small>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="event">
            <div class="event-date">
              <p>The institutionalization process of the Company begins.
              </p>
              <small> 2006</small>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="event">
            <div class="event-date">
              <p>Start of operations in Quintana Roo with the “Villas Otoch I” development.</p>
              <small> 2004</small>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="event ">
            <div class="event-date">
              <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-12">
                  <img src="/assets/cadu/images/content/2004.png" class="img-responsive" alt="CADU">
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="event">
            <div class="event-date">
              <p>Start of operations in Jalisco with the “Villas de Hacienda” development.</p>
              <small> 2003</small>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="event">
            <div class="event-date">
              <p>CADU builds and initiates the commercialization process of its first developments, “Santa Isabel” and “Bajio de las Palmas”, in Aguascalientes.</p>
              <small> 2002</small>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="event mover">
            <div class="event-date">
              <p>Establishment of CADU Inmobiliaria S.A. de C.V. in Aguascalientes.</p>
              <small>2001</small>
            </div>
          </li>

        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</div>
